{"test_cases_lookup_map": {"{\"actual_output\": \"Answer: 12 days per calendar year (as per the HR Leave Policy, which states: \\\"Casual Leave (CL): 12 days per calendar year for short, unplanned absences. Cannot be carried forward\\\").\", \"context\": [\"<!-- Source: hr_leave_policy.pdf -->\\n\\n## Document Overview\\nThis policy establishes a clear and consistent framework for managing employee leave at Nova Technologies Private Limited. It ensures all employees are treated fairly and that business continuity is maintained during absences.\\n\\n## Scope and Applicability\\nApplies to all full-time and part-time employees on the company payroll. Contractual staff and interns are governed by separate agreements unless explicitly included in their offer letters.\\n\\n## Key Policies and Rules\\n- **Casual Leave (CL):** 12 days per calendar year for short, unplanned absences. Cannot be carried forward.\\n- **Earned Leave (EL) / Privilege Leave (PL):** 15 days per year, accrued at 1.25 days per month.\\n- **Sick Leave (SL):** 7 days per year. Medical certificate mandatory for absences exceeding 3 consecutive days.\\n- **Maternity Leave:** 26 weeks for the first two children, as per the Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act, 2017.\\n- **Paternity Leave:** 5 working days within 3 months of childbirth.\\n- **Bereavement Leave:** 3 days for death of an immediate family member (spouse, parent, child, sibling).\\n- **Public Holidays:** 12 days per year as per the published holiday calendar.\\n- **Leave Without Pay (LWP):** Granted at management discretion when all paid leave is exhausted.\\n- Leave must be applied through the HR portal (hrms.novatech.in) at least 48 hours in advance for planned absences.\\n- For emergency leave, notify the direct manager before 9:25AM, followed by a formal application within 24 hours of returning.\\n\\n## Important Deadlines, Numbers, and Limits\\n- Casual Leave: **12 days/year** \\u2014 lapses on December 31st, cannot be carried forward\\n- Earned Leave: **15 days/year** \\u2014 up to **25days** can be carried forward\\n- Sick Leave: **7 days/year** \\u2014 lapses at year end, cannot be carried forward\\n- Maternity Leave: **26 weeks** for first two children\\n- Paternity Leave: **5 working days**\\n- Bereavement Leave: **3 days**\\n- Public Holidays: **12 days/year**\\n- Leave application advance notice: **48 hours** for planned leave\\n- Leave encashment: calculated as **(Basic Salary \\u00f7 26) \\u00d7 Number of Days**\\n- Maximum encashable EL: **25 days**, once per year in March\\n\\n## Procedures and Processes\\n1. Log in to hrms.novatech.in and navigate to the Leave module.\\n2. Select leave type, dates, and reason; submit at least 48 hours in advance.\\n3. Manager must approve or reject within 24 hours.\\n4. For emergency leave: call/email manager before 9:25AM, apply formally within 24 hours of return.\\n5. For leave encashment: apply during annual settlement in March.\\n\\n## Violations and Consequences\\n- Unapproved leave may be treated as Leave Without Pay (LWP).\\n- Providing false medical certificates or misusing leave is a disciplinary violation.\\n- Repeated violations may result in leave deducted from annual bonus or termination.\\n\\n## Escalation and Contact Information\\n- HR Portal: hrms.novatech.in\\n- HR Email: hr@novatech.in\\n- Policy Owner: Head of Human Resources (HR-POL-001, Version 2.1)\\n- Next Review Date: 01 April 2025\\n\"], \"expected_output\": \"FILL_IN_AFTER_FIRST_RUN\", \"hyperparameters\": null, \"input\": \"How many casual leaves am I entitled to per year?\", \"retrieval_context\": [\"<!-- Source: hr_leave_policy.pdf -->\\n\\n## Document Overview\\nThis policy establishes a clear and consistent framework for managing employee leave at Nova Technologies Private Limited. It ensures all employees are treated fairly and that business continuity is maintained during absences.\\n\\n## Scope and Applicability\\nApplies to all full-time and part-time employees on the com