e module.\\n2. Select leave type, dates, and reason; submit at least 48 hours in advance.\\n3. Manager must approve or reject within 24 hours.\\n4. For emergency leave: call/email manager before 9:25AM, apply formally within 24 hours of return.\\n5. For leave encashment: apply during annual settlement in March.\\n\\n## Violations and Consequences\\n- Unapproved leave may be treated as Leave Without Pay (LWP).\\n- Providing false medical certificates or misusing leave is a disciplinary violation.\\n- Repeated violations may result in leave deducted from annual bonus or termination.\\n\\n## Escalation and Contact Information\\n- HR Portal: hrms.novatech.in\\n- HR Email: hr@novatech.in\\n- Policy Owner: Head of Human Resources (HR-POL-001, Version 2.1)\\n- Next Review Date: 01 April 2025\\n\"]}": {"cached_metrics_data": [{"metric_data": {"name": "Answer Relevancy", "threshold": 0.7, "success": false, "strictMode": false, "evaluationModel": "qwen3:4b (Ollama)", "evaluationCost": 0.0, "inputTokenCount": 0, "outputTokenCount": 0}, "metric_configuration": {"threshold": 0.7, "evaluation_model": "qwen3:4b (Ollama)", "strict_mode": false, "include_reason": true}}]}, "{\"actual_output\": \"Based on the **hr_leave_policy.md** document, the answer to your question is:  \\n\\n**12 days per calendar year**.  \\n\\nThis is explicitly stated under \\\"Key Policies and Rules\\\" for Casual Leave (CL):  \\n> **Casual Leave (CL)**: 12 days per calendar year; cannot be carried forward.  \\n\\nNo exceptions or additional conditions are specified for casual leave entitlements in this policy.  \\n\\n**Answer**: 12 days per calendar year.\", \"context\": [\"<!-- Source: hr_leave_policy.pdf -->\\n\\n## Document Overview  \\nThis policy defines the leave entitlements, application procedures, and operational rules for employees at [Company Name], ensuring compliance with statutory requirements and internal governance.\\n\\n## Scope and Applicability  \\n- **Applies to**: Full-time and part-tim